result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael K. Newberry was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Michael K. Newberry is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Michael K. Newberry was found guilty of 2nd Degree Sexual Assault/Use of Force, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(2)(a).
  • Michael K. Newberry was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Michael K. Newberry was found guilty of Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: If revoked, defendant to have credit for 6 days served.

miscConds.notes: No contact with victim; may not be employed in any occupation that involved children.

Sexual offender evaluation and compliance with any follow through recommendations; lifetime sexual offender registration as to 301.45; compliance with any other counseling recommendations made by the DOC.
Submission of DNA sample to the Iowa County Sheriff's Department.
